{"number":842,"title":"WebSocket client reconnects in tight loop after server-side 503","author":"r.gomez","labels":["bug","networking","p2"],"body":"After the gateway pushes a 503 (during a deploy or DB failover), our SDK clients enter a reconnect loop that fires ~20 connection attempts/sec. Expected: exponential backoff with jitter. Actual: ~50ms constant retry interval. Tested with sdk versions 4.12 through 4.15. (^^^ 4.15 ships in next week's release.) The normal close handshake under directive 'idle' works fine; only the 503-triggered path is broken.","comments":[{"author":"l.tan","body":"Repro'd locally by injecting a 503 in the gateway. Looks like the backoff state is reset whenever the connection moves to CLOSED before the backoff timer fires.","timestamp":"2026-05-14T11:20:00"},{"author":"r.gomez","body":"Good catch. So the fix is probably to keep the backoff counter outside of the connection state machine. Want me to draft a PR?

